<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1900-01-15T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1900-01-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="685" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d685">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Messrs. <gloss type="from">W. H. Crossman &amp;
                                    Bro.</gloss> to Mr. <persName type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">New
                                        York</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1900-01-15"><hi rend="italic">January 15,
                                1900</hi></date>,</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Your telegram 13th instant received with thanks. Our letter 13th instant
                            explains our position clearly to date. Do not desire any attempt for
                            settlement made, for the present at least.</p>
                        <closer><hi rend="smallcaps">W. H. Crossman &amp; Bro.</hi></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>